INSERT INTO `cmsplugin_text` VALUES (1,'<h3>Our distillery is located in one of the most beautful regions of Britain, the Lake District.</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"250\" src=\"/media/files/frozen-bass.gif\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 250px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; border: 0; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\" width=\"660\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our distillery is in a region renowned for its beauty, its dramatic landscapes and, of course, magnificent lakes.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After more than two years of searching, we have at last found what we believe to be the perfect site - close to Bassenthwaite Lake, six miles from the capital of the North Lakes, Keswick.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Encircled by Cumbrian hills and mountains, it is an area of unimaginable beauty.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unchanged for centuries, the only sounds are the cry of ospreys, the gentle trickle of water from the streams which feed the lake itself and, of course, the soft rain falling on the heather and grass. One of the Lakes highest peaks, Skiddaw, watches over the lake, an inspiration to poets including Wordsworth and Tennyson.</p>\n<p>This is the home of the new Lakes Distillery. <img alt=\"\" height=\"250\" src=\"/media/files/bassenthwaite_1..jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 250px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; border: 0; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\" width=\"660\"></p>\n<h3>WHISKY IN CUMBRIA</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cumbria has a long whisky heritage, and if look around the Lakes, you will see exactly why. The landscape is one of fast flowing rivers, rugged mountains and clean pure air - these conditions are very much like those found in Scotland.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"436\" src=\"/media/files/whisky-map.gif\" style=\"width: 263px; height: 300px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; float: left; border: 0; margin: 5px 15px 5px 0;\" width=\"382\"> The Lake District in Cumbria was also once part of Scotland. Its place names reflect its celtic heritage. It is remote, wet and beautiful. In short, it is ideal whisky producing country.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With this perfect environment for making whisky, it is no surprise that there is also a long history of illicit whisky distilling in the area, with the secluded hills and valleys of the area ideal for smugglers. One of these distillers was Lancelot \'Lanty\' Slee, who had a thriving business and always managed to keep one step ahead of the customs authorities  helped by supplying his \'whisky\' to the local magistrates. With many other illicit stills in the Lakes, the area was well known as a whisky producing region at this time.</p>'),(112,'<h3><span>You will be able to see here our artisan bar and bistros delicious menu.</span></h3>'),(142,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 459px; width: 951px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"451\" src=\"/media/files/brand/the_lakes_malt.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"362\"></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<h1>THE LAKES MALT</h1>\n<h3><span><span>The Lakes Malt will be available from 2019.</span></span></h3>\n<p>Most of the malt whisky we will produce will be lightly peated, so more akin to the whiskies from the highlands rather than Islay, although we do plan to run some batches of a more heavily peated malt each year.</p>\n<p><span>Our team is steeped in whisky experience. Our founder,</span><a href=\"http://213.175.215.219/~lakes2/our%20people/our-people/our-people/our-distillery/our-people/paul-currie\">Paul Currie</a><span>, co-founded the widely acclaimed, award winning Arran distillery, and our production is overseen by one of Scotlands foremost whisky experts,</span><a href=\"http://213.175.215.219/~lakes2/our-people/our-people/our-distillery/our-people/alan-rutherford\">Alan Rutherford</a><span>, former production director at Diageo and council member of the Scotch Whisky Association.</span></p>\n<p>Our master distiller<a href=\"http://213.175.215.219/~lakes2/our-distillery/our-people/chris-anderson\">Chris Anderson</a>will be crossing the border from Scotland, with a lifetimes experience of making the highest quality whisky, including as manager of a number of well known distilleries.</p>\n<p>The Lakes Malt will become available only once it is perfectly matured - so we will have to be patient for a little while yet!</p>\n<p>You can secure your own bottlings taken from the first 100 casks ever produced of The Lakes Malt by joining our Founders\' Club -<a href=\"/admin/cms/page/54/edit-plugin/142/founders-club\" target=\"_self\">Click Here</a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(186,'<table style=\"height: 310px; width: 901px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_chris_anderson_(2).jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>CHRIS ANDERSON - MASTER DISTILLER</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>\"Most of all Im looking forward to seeing the first spirit flow into the spirit safe. Then the adventure really begins.\"</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Chris Anderson comes from a long line of Scottish whisky distillers and began his own whisky career at CaolIla on Islay. He also worked at Lagavulin before moving to manage all of Dewars distilleries, including Royal Brackla, Aberfeldy, Craigellachie and Aultmore. Chris brings a wealth of experience to us, as he will play the central role in creating the new Lakes Malt.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(187,'<table style=\"height: 308px; width: 905px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_alan_rutherford.jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>DR ALAN RUTHERFORD OBE - DIRECTOR</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>The Lakes Distillery has so much going for it  a great team, a wonderful location, and all the ingredients for what should be an outstanding malt whisky</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Alan Rutherford, whose career in the whisky industry spans almost 40 years, is one of the leading figures in the whisky industry. A former council member of the Scotch Whisky Council, he was previously scotch whisky production director at United Distillers - later Diageo. Alan will oversee the production of our whiskies and gin.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(199,'<hr>\n<h2><img alt=\"\" height=\"127\" src=\"/media/files/the_paul_currie_story/paul-revised-quote.gif\" style=\"font-size: 10px;\" width=\"659\"></h2>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n<p>Whiskys been a part of my life for as long as I can remember. My father was MD of Chivas-Seagrams whisky business - so, from birth, whisky was a constant topic of conversation and a genuine family passion.</p>\n<p>As a child I was fascinated by the process of distilling and I can clearly recall being taken round a distillery for the first time  I think I would have been about six-years-old  and being entranced by the gleaming copper stills.</p>\n<p>That early fascination with whisky developed over the years and in 1995 I set up Isle of Arran Distillers with my father  at the time it was the first new independent whisky distillery in Scotland for many decades but we could see the potential growth in malt whisky and we werent wrong: the whisky market and, in particular the malt whisky market, has gone from strength to strength ever since.As managing director of the company I oversaw the successful opening of the distillery, products were launched in Europe, Asia and north America, and a number of prestigious awards were won  including Scottish TVs Best Young Business and Scottish Trade Internationals New Exporter of the Year. The company received royal recognition when the visitor centre was officially opened by HM The Queen, and it also received a coveted 5 Star Visit Scotland award.</p>\n<p>I moved on from Arran to pursue other interests in the spirits industry, but then, around three years or so ago, I was on holiday in the Lake District with my family and as I looked around at the magnificent landscape; the lakes, the peaty foothills, the pure air, I realised this really was perfect whisky country and thats how The Lakes Distillery was born.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"212\" src=\"/media/files/the_paul_currie_story/pc_with_queen_arran_opening_(2)_small.jpg\" style=\"float: right;\" width=\"300\"></p>\n<p>Malt whisky is a booming industry with new distilleries being created across the world in countries as diverse as the US, Australia, France, Sweden and India. This was proof, if I needed it, that consumers are keen to try products from new distilleries  so why not The Lakes Distillery?</p>\n<p>The vision was one thing, however turning it into reality was quite another. One of my brothers, also involved in the whisky industry, tried to set up a distillery in the south Lakes about 10 years ago, but couldnt secure the right location and couldnt put the funding together, so I knew this would not be easy.</p>\n<p>From experience I know how important it is to build a team, and so I set about putting this in place. Newcastle-based retail expert Nigel Mills has taken on the role of Chairman, and some true whisky experts have joined us, including our master distiller, Chris Anderson, whose wealth of experience and knowledge is second to none.</p>\n<p>Then, we needed to find a site and this was a huge challenge. Because the Lake District is a National Park, any development, quite rightly,is very controlled.</p>\n<p>We needed to be able to utilise existing buildings and they needed to be the right size, not only for a distillery with enough height to accommodate the stills, but for a visitor centre and with adequate access, both for deliveries and for our tourist business.</p>\n<p>Most importantly, however, we had to have a nearby source of water  and not just any water but the water that would provide the basis of The Lakes Malt.</p>\n<p>We looked at one site after another and I spent countless days poring over a map trying to work out suitable locations and driving around in the hope of spotting the perfect site  I got to know the Lakes very well!</p>\n<p>Then I contacted a property agent in Keswick, who proposed a site at Bassenthwaite Lake. It was an old Victorian Model Farm, built in the 1850s and used as a dairy farm until about 15 years ago, since it when it had stood empty.</p>\n<p>Plans were sent through and it looked very promising so we arranged for me to visit the site and meet the owner. My first impressions were all good  and then I saw the main barn and my mind was made up. Id found my distillery.</p>\n<p>Not only was it visually stunning but I reckoned it would be tall enough for our stills  better still, the river Derwent was only 150m away, so there was our water supply.</p>\n<p>The owner, Keith Fisher, seemed very supportive of our plans,so it was looking hopeful, but there was a very long way to go.</p>\n<p>Detailed plans were sent through and they confirmed that the buildings were big enough and tall enough. It also transpired we could take a wooded area next to the site to use for parking and we could also use the field between the buildings and the river, so we could have our water supply.</p>\n<p>The next stage was to agree a deal for the site, get architects drawings done and, crucially, apply for planning permission.</p>\n<p>Agreement was reached on the commercial terms for the property, so that was one hurdle out of the way.</p>\n<p>However, we also felt local support was important, so I held a meeting in the village hall to explain our plans. I wasnt sure how many would come, but the hall was packed!</p>\n<p>Understandably, there was a great deal of curiosity but this was an ideal opportunity to answer questions and provide reassurance that our aim was for The Lakes Distillery to be a true asset to the area  and would create much needed local employment.</p>\n<p>We couldnt have wished for greater support, not just from our soon-to-be neighbours but from the parish council, which subsequently gave us its full backing.</p>\n<p>We were on our way. Plans were drawn up by our architects, Architects Plus, structural surveys done (the buildings are actually in surprisingly good condition) and an excellent planning consultant, Bruce Armstrong Payne, helped us put together the planning application  not as straightforward a process as you might think.</p>\n<p>Planning applications require input from so many organisations; the parish council, DEFRA, Natural England, Cumbria Tourism, the Highways Agency  but, thankfully, all gave us their full support.</p>\n<p>At the first planning meeting, it was decided that the planning committee would do a site visit. This was done in pouring rain and a gale force wind, but the committee seemed to love the site and, at the next meeting, we were granted permission with a unanimous vote in favour.</p>\n<p>The next step was to complete the legal work on the property  a lengthy process  and then it was ours. We were ready to go.</p>\n<p>There is still a great deal to do, but work has now begun on the site and my dream, the dream which began three years ago, inspired by my lifelong love for whisky, is coming true.</p>\n<p>And that is certainly worth raising a glass to.</p>'),(212,'<table style=\"height: 308px; width: 838px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/paul_currie_at_site.jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>PAUL CURRIE - FOUNDER AND MANAGING DIRECTOR</h1>\n<hr>\n<p><span><span><span>Whiskys been a part of my life for as long as I can remember.</span></span></span></p>\n<hr>\n<p>With a family background in the whisky industry, he has had a lifelong love of spirits, and previously set up the award winning Isle of Arran distillery with his father. He has been the driving force behind setting up the new Lakes Distillery.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(217,'<h3>Production will start in Spring 2014, with the visitor centre opening in the autumn.</h3>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 270px; width: 455px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"10\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"644\" src=\"/media/files/timetable/timetable_(2).gif\" width=\"161\"></td>\n<td>\n<p><span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong>September 2013</strong></em></span></span></p>\n<p><span>- Launch of<a href=\"/shop\">The ONE</a>at the Taste Cumbria festival</span></p>\n<p><span><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">October 2013</span></em></strong></span></p>\n<p><span>- Final stages of planning being approved</span></p>\n<p><span>- Interior designers working on their initial concepts</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong>November 2013</strong></em></span></p>\n<p>- Work to start on site</p>\n<p>- Gift packs and miniature gift packs launched in time for Christmas!</p>\n<p>- The Wine Chambers Christmas tasting at the Grand Hotel - Tynemouth, Newcastle Upon Tyne. 27th &amp; 28th 5pm - 9pm</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><em>Spring 2014</em></strong></span></p>\n<p>- The stills will be delivered allowing us to start the production of The Lakes Gin, and The Lakes Malt straight away</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><em>Autumn 2014</em></strong></span></p>\n<p>- We hope to have the remaining building work completed for our Visitor Centre, Bistro &amp; Bar and Shop</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(221,'<h3><span>You will be able to go inside the distillery to see exactly how The Lakes Malt and The Lakes Gin are made, as well as being able to visit our warehouse filled with our maturing whisky.</span></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/media/files/destillery_tours/slate.gif\" width=\"660\" alt=\"\" height=\"126\"></p>\n<p>The Lake District is a hugely popular tourist area, and we aim to be a major attraction to the 15 million visitors who come each year.<img src=\"/media/files/destillery_tours/archway-in-dis.gif\" width=\"200\" style=\"float: right;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p>The tour will start in an information area which will include a video, and your expert, entertaining guide will then take you through to the distillery to reveal the secrets of how malt whisky and gin are made. You will be taken through the warehouse, where our whisky peacefully matures in casks, and on to our tasting room, where you can taste our products for yourself.</p>\n<p></p>'),(430,'<h3><span>The ONE is not only perfect alone but great in cocktails. We have had some fantastic cocktail tutorial videos created so you too can make you own cocktails with The ONE.</span></h3>'),(431,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 296px; width: 597px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE SOUR ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE OLD ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"147\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/thesourone-easy.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/sour-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"147\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/thesourone-easy.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/old-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"147\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/theoldone-advanced.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\"><hr></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE IRISH ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE BLUE ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE SMOKEY ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/irish-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"148\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/theirishone-medium.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/blue-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"148\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/theblueone-medium.jpg\" width=\"196\"></a></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/smokey-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"148\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/thesmokeyone-medium.jpg\" width=\"196\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\"><hr></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE STRAWBERRY</span><br><span style=\"font-size: large;\">SOUR ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: large;\"></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/strawberry-sour-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"147\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/thestrawberrysourone-medium.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><hr></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(442,'<table style=\"height: 194px; width: 579px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/scone.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/while_you_decide.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/north_atlantic_prawn.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0110.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0122.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0152.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(459,'<h3><span>We will be converting one of the byres at the site into a very special private dining facility, with access into our warehouse for exclusive tastings.</span></h3>'),(600,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 511px; width: 913px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"449\" src=\"/media/files/brand/the_one_bottle.jpg\" width=\"367\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>THE ONE213123</h1>\n<p></p>\n<h3><span><span>The One is a unique blend of exceptional whiskies from the British Isles.</span></span></h3>\n<p>Each has its own distinctive characteristics, resulting in a whisky of intriguing complexity.</p>\n<p>There are now distilleries producing whisky across the British Isles, and this has led us to create an entirely new concept in blended whiskies - a British Isles Blend.</p>\n<p>To create \'The One\', we have searched far and wide to bring together a range of very special whiskies from the British Isles. These have been blended with great care and passion to create a perfectly balanced whisky.</p>\n<h3><span><span>Tasting Notes</span></span></h3>\n<p>Slightly smoky, sweet and fruity, nutty, with hints of spice.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p></p>\n<h3><span><span><span>Reviews</span></span></span></h3>\n<p><span>A really quality blend this, crafted with obvious love<em>-<strong>Somerset Whisky Blog - Score 87</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><span>Very nice. Well rounded sweet and spicy. A very enjoyable little blend, and not very expensive too. Lovely -<strong><em>Whisky Isreal - Score 84</em></strong></span></p>\n<p><span>The One is a good solid blend and well worth considering as we move into the winter months -<strong><em>Living Room Whisky</em></strong></span></p>\n<p><span>The design is simple and gorgeous</span></p>\n<p><span>Lovelycreamy sweet vanillafudgenote</span></p>\n<p><span>Its nicely sweet and well balanced</span></p>\n<p><span>Very nice blend - recommend</span></p>\n<p><span>Both The One whisky and Cumbria are equally beautiful</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"/media/files/brand/banner/bottom_banner_(1).jpg\" width=\"1000\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(710,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 232px; width: 602px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">INGREDIENTS<br><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">(For one cocktail)</span></h1>\n<table align=\"right\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"tb-data\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">37.5ml</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The One</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">250ml</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Gomme</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">12.5ml</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lemon Juice</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">3 drops</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"fon