medium;\">Gomme</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">12.5ml</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lemon Juice</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">25ml</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Strawberry Puree</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">3 drops</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Bitters NO MORE</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><br>EQUIPMENT</h1>\n<table align=\"right\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"tb-data\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">Glass:</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Rocks/Collins</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">Garnish:</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lemon Wedge</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"794\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/full-image.jpg\" width=\"343\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(894,'<h3>Our distillery is located in one of the most beautful regions of Britain, the Lake District.</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"/media/files/frozen-bass.gif\" width=\"660\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 250px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; border: 0; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\" height=\"250\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our distillery is in a region renowned for its beauty, its dramatic landscapes and, of course, magnificent lakes.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After more than two years of searching, we have at last found what we believe to be the perfect site - close to Bassenthwaite Lake, six miles from the capital of the North Lakes, Keswick.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Encircled by Cumbrian hills and mountains, it is an area of unimaginable beauty.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unchanged for centuries, the only sounds are the cry of ospreys, the gentle trickle of water from the streams which feed the lake itself and, of course, the soft rain falling on the heather and grass. One of the Lakes highest peaks, Skiddaw, watches over the lake, an inspiration to poets including Wordsworth and Tennyson.</p>\n<p>This is the home of the new Lakes Distillery. <img src=\"/media/files/our-site-lakes.gif\" width=\"660\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 250px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; border: 0; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\" height=\"250\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<h3>WHISKY IN CUMBRIA</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cumbria has a long whisky heritage, and if look around the Lakes, you will see exactly why. The landscape is one of fast flowing rivers, rugged mountains and clean pure air - these conditions are very much like those found in Scotland.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"/media/files/whisky-map.gif\" width=\"382\" style=\"width: 263px; height: 300px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; float: left; border: 0; margin: 5px 15px 5px 0;\" height=\"436\" alt=\"\"> The Lake District in Cumbria was also once part of Scotland. Its place names reflect its celtic heritage. It is remote, wet and beautiful. In short, it is ideal whisky producing country.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With this perfect environment for making whisky, it is no surprise that there is also a long history of illicit whisky distilling in the area, with the secluded hills and valleys of the area ideal for smugglers. One of these distillers was Lancelot \'Lanty\' Slee, who had a thriving business and always managed to keep one step ahead of the customs authorities  helped by supplying his \'whisky\' to the local magistrates. With many other illicit stills in the Lakes, the area was well known as a whisky producing region at this time.</p>'),(926,'<h3><span style=\"font-size: small;\">We are renovating the historic buildings of an old Victorian Model Farm next to the famous river Derwent and close to the lake, and there we aim to produce a world class single malt whisky. Check in on our progress on our webcams below</span></h3>'),(928,'<h2>Webcam 1 - Construction View</h2>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(930,'<hr>\n<h2>Webcam 2 - River View</h2>\n<hr>\n<h1></h1>'),(1101,'<h1>Partner Scheme</h1>'),(1104,'<p>1. Choose which banner you would like to use</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>2. Email us on <a href=\"mailto:partners@lakesdistillery.com\" target=\"_blank\">partners@lakesdistillery.com</a> with your choice</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>3. We will then send you the banner with your unique code, so that sales can be tracked to you</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>4. You then put this up on your website, and that\'s it! </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>You may also want to feature information about our clubs on your site - full details can be found in the members dropdown on the website.</p>'),(1152,'<h3><span>The ONE is not only perfect alone but great in cocktails. We have had some fantastic cocktail tutorial videos created so you too can make you own cocktails with The ONE.</span></h3>'),(1153,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 250px; width: 596px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">INGREDIENTS<br><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">(For one cocktail)</span></h1>\n<table align=\"right\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"tb-data\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">50ml</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The One</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">1</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Ice Ball</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">EQUIPMENT</h1>\n<table align=\"right\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"tb-data\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"left-heading\" style=\"text-align: right;\" width=\"40%\"><span style=\"color: #888888; font-size: medium;\">Glass:</span></td>\n<td class=\"right-heading\" width=\"60%\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Rocks</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"794\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/full-image.jpg\" width=\"343\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(1547,'<h3>Our distillery is located in one of the most beautful regions of Britain, the Lake District.</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"250\" src=\"/media/files/frozen-bass.gif\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 250px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; border: 0; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\" width=\"660\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our distillery is in a region renowned for its beauty, its dramatic landscapes and, of course, magnificent lakes.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After more than two years of searching, we have at last found what we believe to be the perfect site - close to Bassenthwaite Lake, six miles from the capital of the North Lakes, Keswick.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Encircled by Cumbrian hills and mountains, it is an area of unimaginable beauty.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unchanged for centuries, the only sounds are the cry of ospreys, the gentle trickle of water from the streams which feed the lake itself and, of course, the soft rain falling on the heather and grass. One of the Lakes highest peaks, Skiddaw, watches over the lake, an inspiration to poets including Wordsworth and Tennyson.</p>\n<p>This is the home of the new Lakes Distillery. <img alt=\"\" height=\"250\" src=\"/media/files/bassenthwaite_1..jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 250px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; border: 0; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\" width=\"660\"></p>\n<h3>WHISKY IN CUMBRIA</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cumbria has a long whisky heritage, and if look around the Lakes, you will see exactly why. The landscape is one of fast flowing rivers, rugged mountains and clean pure air - these conditions are very much like those found in Scotland.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"436\" src=\"/media/files/whisky-map.gif\" style=\"width: 263px; height: 300px; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; float: left; border: 0; margin: 5px 15px 5px 0;\" width=\"382\"> The Lake District in Cumbria was also once part of Scotland. Its place names reflect its celtic heritage. It is remote, wet and beautiful. In short, it is ideal whisky producing country.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With this perfect environment for making whisky, it is no surprise that there is also a long history of illicit whisky distilling in the area, with the secluded hills and valleys of the area ideal for smugglers. One of these distillers was Lancelot \'Lanty\' Slee, who had a thriving business and always managed to keep one step ahead of the customs authorities  helped by supplying his \'whisky\' to the local magistrates. With many other illicit stills in the Lakes, the area was well known as a whisky producing region at this time.</p>'),(1559,'<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The distillery is located next to Bassenthwaite Lake, which is a National Nature Reserve in one of Britain\'s most beautiful areas, the Lake District.</span></h3>'),(1561,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Close to Bassenthwaite Lake, in an area of unimaginable beauty encircled by Cumbrian fells, we have found the perfect home for the new Lakes Distillery.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are renovating the historic buildings of an old Victorian Model Farm next to the famous river Derwent and close to Bassenthwaite Lake, and there we aim to produce a world class single malt whisky.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have ideal water from the famous River Derwent, with its source high up in the fells, a team steeped in whisky experience, and perfect conditions for distilling.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Derwent\'s source is at Sprinkling Tarn, one of the most beautiful tarns in Cumbria, and from there it flows down through the peaty foothills, which surround Scafell Pike, the highest of the Lakes\' peaks. It is a famous salmon river, and the area where it flows past our distillery has been designated a site of Special Scientific Interest. Analysis has shown it contains all the vital constituents necessary for distilling the purest whisky  but that is just the start of the process.</p>'),(1563,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have put a lot of thought into the production process at our distillery to ensure we produce a malt whisky of outstanding quality. The plant has been carefully designed to the highest specification, and our copper stills will be made to a unique design and on a small artisan scale  no mass production for us!</span><span style=\"font-size: medium; text-align: justify;\"><br></span></p>'),(1565,'<p></p>\n<hr>\n<h1><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\"><strong>A \'GREEN\' WHISKY</strong></span></h1>\n<hr>\n<p><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Producing our whisky in the most environmentally friendly way possible is very important to us, and we will be doing everything possible to reduce our carbon footprint.</span></em></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><hr><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The whisky production process is entirely natural, using only grain, yeast and water. No damaging effluent is produced.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Most of the by-products from the distillation processes will be returned to local farmers for use as animal feed and for soil improvement.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Water used for production will be stored and recycled.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Heat from the distillation process will be reused to heat all the buildings (including the visitor centre), and natural ventilation and river water will be used for cooling.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Building materials will be as eco friendly as possible (eg wool insulation in the walls).</span></span></li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>'),(1610,'<h3>We are renovating the historic buildings of an old Victorian Model Farm next to the famous river Derwent and close to the lake, and there we aim to produce a world class single malt whisky.</h3>'),(1611,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 212px; width: 291px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Model farms were designed to be beautiful as well as functional  and our buildings are certainly beautiful and ideally suited to our needs. Each one is being carefully and sympathetically adapted, preserving the character and history of the old,stone-built barns and sheds.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"221\" src=\"/media/files/our_buildings/dsc04148.jpg\" width=\"629\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<p>The main barn will house our mash house and still house, with our unique stills, carefully designed to produce our Lakes Malt and Lakes Gin. An old cattle shed will be converted into our warehouse, with further cattle sheds being transformed into our shop and bistro. We think that Jos Christopherson, who farmed here in 1847, would have approved. Perhaps he even had an illicit still at the farm?</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(1623,'<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This quatrefoil design of a four leaf clover can be foun<img alt=\"\" height=\"152\" src=\"/media/files/hope,_faith,_luck,_love_v6_.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 15px; float: left;\" width=\"250\">d throughout the distillery buildings  representing hope, faith, love and luck. We hope to have all four in abundance!</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"></span></p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(1796,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(1797,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(1879,'<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">VIEW OUR E-BROCHURE</h3>'),(1882,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(1883,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(1885,'<h3><span>Imagine if you could own one of the first bottles produced of one of the great single malts - well now you can. Strictly limited to the first 2975 applicants.</span></h3>'),(1926,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">By becoming a member of our Founders Club, you can join us on our journey, by receiving the very first bottles of the maturing Lakes Malt taken from the first 100 casks to be produced at the distillery.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is How it Works...</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will set aside the first 100 casks produced at the Lakes Distillery and we will bottle the maturing whisky for Founders Club members.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Each year for ten years you will receive one 70cl bottle giving you a collectible set of the distillerys first ever production, all with unique, limited edition labels. You will also receive two miniatures each year so you will have the rare opportunity to taste the spirit as it develops over time into a wonderful, single malt whisky. Delivery of the first bottle will be in 2015.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">These casks will not be available to the general public  only to members.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you join, you will also receive a membership pack with your certificate.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On-going benefits will include a bi-monthly newsletter with rare, limited edition offers, web cam access so you can follow all our progress at The Lakes Distillery and discount vouchers on food, beverages and distillery tours.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This offer will never be repeated. It is a rare opportunity to own a piece of historic whisky distilling.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">These first casks can only ever be produced once  so this is YOUR chance to own a piece of whisky history. Its going to be fascinating seeing how our spirit matures and we want connoisseurs and friends of the Lakes to be part of the journey.</p>'),(2457,'<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"620\" src=\"/media/files/the_bar_and_bistro/545_big.jpg\" style=\"vertical-align: text-top;\" width=\"620\"></p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(2462,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Work is now underway to convert one of our cattle sheds into a bar and bistro which we hope will be the perfect place in which to sample some truly impressive whisky, gin and vodka alongside a menu full of locally-sourced and seasonal dishes.</p>'),(2465,'<h3><span>From Cumbrian cheeses to lamb and fish, the region is a cornucopia of great ingredients and our bar will stock wines, local ales and whiskies hand-picked to complement them.</span></h3>'),(2466,'<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many before us have realised that this unspoiled corner of Britain is a treasure trove of ingredients and resources, and consequently the Lake District is home to numerous artisan food producers and craftsmen  all working with their surroundings to create something special. From Cumbrian cheeses to lamb and fish, the region is a cornucopia of great ingredients and our bar will stock wines, local ales and whiskies hand-picked to complement them.It has been our aim, from the early stages of planning The Lakes Distillery that, not only will our visitors be able to learn all about The Lakes Malt, The Lakes Gin &amp; The Lakes Vodka they will be able to see and taste for themselves other local produce in our artisan bar &amp; bistro.</p>'),(2508,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(2569,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(2635,'<table style=\"height: 308px; width: 838px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/paul_currie_at_site.jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>PAUL CURRIE - FOUNDER AND MANAGING DIRECTOR</h1>\n<hr>\n<p><span><span><span>Whiskys been a part of my life for as long as I can remember.</span></span></span></p>\n<hr>\n<p>With a family background in the whisky industry, he has had a lifelong love of spirits, and previously set up the award winning Isle of Arran distillery with his father. He has been the driving force behind setting up the new Lakes Distillery.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(2636,'<table style=\"height: 308px; width: 905px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_alan_rutherford.jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>DR ALAN RUTHERFORD OBE - DIRECTOR</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>The Lakes Distillery has so much going for it  a great team, a wonderful location, and all the ingredients for what should be an outstanding malt whisky</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Alan Rutherford, whose career in the whisky industry spans almost 40 years, is one of the leading figures in the whisky industry. A former council member of the Scotch Whisky Council, he was previously scotch whisky production director at United Distillers - later Diageo. Alan will oversee the production of our whiskies and gin.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(2637,'<table style=\"height: 310px; width: 901px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_chris_anderson_(2).jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>CHRIS ANDERSON - MASTER DISTILLER</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>\"Most of all Im looking forward to seeing the first spirit flow into the spirit safe. Then the adventure really begins.\"</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Chris Anderson comes from a long line of Scottish whisky distillers and began his own whisky career at CaolIla on Islay. He also worked at Lagavulin before moving to manage all of Dewars distilleries, including Royal Brackla, Aberfeldy, Craigellachie and Aultmore. Chris brings a wealth of experience to us, as he will play the central role in creating the new Lakes Malt.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(2660,'<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"620\" src=\"/media/files/the_bar_and_bistro/545_big.jpg\" style=\"vertical-align: text-top;\" width=\"620\"></p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(2665,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Work is now underway to convert one of our cattle sheds into a bar and bistro which we hope will be the perfect place in which to sample some truly impressive Whisky, Gin and Vodka alongside a menu full of locally-sourced and seasonal dishes.</p>'),(2667,'<h3><span>From Cumbrian cheeses to lamb and fish, the region is a cornucopia of great ingredients and our bar will stock wines, local ales and whiskies hand-picked to complement them.</span></h3>'),(2668,'<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many before us have realised that this unspoiled corner of Britain is a treasu