ater  and not just any water but the water that would provide the basis of The Lakes Malt.</p>\n<p>We looked at one site after another and I spent countless days poring over a map trying to work out suitable locations and driving around in the hope of spotting the perfect site  I got to know the Lakes very well!</p>\n<p>Then I contacted a property agent in Keswick, who proposed a site at Bassenthwaite Lake. It was an old Victorian Model Farm, built in the 1850s and used as a dairy farm until about 15 years ago, since it when it had stood empty.</p>\n<p>Plans were sent through and it looked very promising so we arranged for me to visit the site and meet the owner. My first impressions were all good  and then I saw the main barn and my mind was made up. Id found my distillery.</p>\n<p>Not only was it visually stunning but I reckoned it would be tall enough for our stills  better still, the river Derwent was only 150m away, so there was our water supply.</p>\n<p>The owner, Keith Fisher, seemed very supportive of our plans,so it was looking hopeful, but there was a very long way to go.</p>\n<p>Detailed plans were sent through and they confirmed that the buildings were big enough and tall enough. It also transpired we could take a wooded area next to the site to use for parking and we could also use the field between the buildings and the river, so we could have our water supply.</p>\n<p>The next stage was to agree a deal for the site, get architects drawings done and, crucially, apply for planning permission.</p>\n<p>Agreement was reached on the commercial terms for the property, so that was one hurdle out of the way.</p>\n<p>However, we also felt local support was important, so I held a meeting in the village hall to explain our plans. I wasnt sure how many would come, but the hall was packed!</p>\n<p>Understandably, there was a great deal of curiosity but this was an ideal opportunity to answer questions and provide reassurance that our aim was for The Lakes Distillery to be a true asset to the area  and would create much needed local employment.</p>\n<p>We couldnt have wished for greater support, not just from our soon-to-be neighbours but from the parish council, which subsequently gave us its full backing.</p>\n<p>We were on our way. Plans were drawn up by our architects, Architects Plus, structural surveys done (the buildings are actually in surprisingly good condition) and an excellent planning consultant, Bruce Armstrong Payne, helped us put together the planning application  not as straightforward a process as you might think.</p>\n<p>Planning applications require input from so many organisations; the parish council, DEFRA, Natural England, Cumbria Tourism, the Highways Agency  but, thankfully, all gave us their full support.</p>\n<p>At the first planning meeting, it was decided that the planning committee would do a site visit. This was done in pouring rain and a gale force wind, but the committee seemed to love the site and, at the next meeting, we were granted permission with a unanimous vote in favour.</p>\n<p>The next step was to complete the legal work on the property  a lengthy process  and then it was ours. We were ready to go.</p>\n<p>There is still a great deal to do, but work has now begun on the site and my dream, the dream which began three years ago, inspired by my lifelong love for whisky, is coming true.</p>\n<p>And that is certainly worth raising a glass to.</p>'),(3652,'<h1>This is how it works...</h1>'),(3743,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 741px; width: 882px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"449\" src=\"/media/files/the_lakes_vodka_(front).jpg\" width=\"367\"></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<h1>THE LAKES VODKA</h1>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n<p>The Lakes Vodka will be the first ever vodka to be produced in Cumbria, lovingly distilled in our small artisan still.</p>\n<p>Vodka has never been produced in Cumbria before, but we are creating something very special.</p>\n<p>We have the ideal ingredients to make a very delicious vodka, and using traditional artisan methods with our beautiful copper pot still, we will be producing a spirit of outstanding quality. And our vodka will be double distilled, making it even purer and smoother.</p>\n<p>The Lakes Vodka - the only vodka to be distilled in Cumbria.</p>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(3760,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 741px; width: 882px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"449\" src=\"/media/files/the_lakes_vodka_(front).jpg\" width=\"367\"></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<h1>THE LAKES VODKA</h1>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n<p>The Lakes Vodka will be the first ever vodka to be produced in Cumbria, lovingly distilled in our small artisan still.</p>\n<p>Vodka has never been produced in Cumbria before, but we are creating something very special.</p>\n<p>We have the ideal ingredients to make a very delicious vodka, and using traditional artisan methods with our beautiful copper pot still, we will be producing a spirit of outstanding quality. And our vodka will be double distilled, making it even purer and smoother.</p>\n<p>The Lakes Vodka - the only vodka to be distilled in Cumbria.</p>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(3770,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(3776,'<p>1. Choose which banner you would like to use</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>2. Email us on <a href=\"mailto:partners@lakesdistillery.com\" target=\"_blank\">partners@lakesdistillery.com</a> with your choice</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>3. We will then send you the banner with your unique code, so that sales can be tracked to you</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>4. You then put this up on your website, and that\'s it! </p>\n<p></p>\n<p>You may also want to feature information about our clubs on your site - full details can be found in the members dropdown on the website.</p>'),(3778,'<h1>This is how it works...</h1>'),(3779,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(3780,'<h1>Partner Scheme</h1>'),(3790,'<p></p>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 237px; width: 777px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"449\" src=\"/media/files/brand/the_lakes_gin_2.jpg\" width=\"367\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>THE LAKES GIN</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Lakes Gin will be the only gin distilled in the Lake District, and will be available from Summer 2014.</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The LakesGinwill be a truly Cumbriangin, made with local botanicals, and distilled in our small artisan still.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The onlyginto be distilled in Cumbria, The LakesGinis a truly unique product. It will be carefully crafted using classicginbotanicals augmented with those native to Cumbria - including juniper, bilberry, heather and meadowsweet.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Made very much on an artisan, small batch scale, it will be lovingly created in our small 1,000 litre still, perfectly designed to produce an outstanding spirit. Instead of the rapid distillation found in most other mass producedgins, ours will be produced over 24 hours - very slowly, very carefully, very delicious.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\">Gin in Cumbria</span></h1>\n<hr><br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cumbria has a rich history of gin - not surprising when it is the main area in the UK where juniper grows.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Throughout the 18th century gin production in the Lake District flourished as, despite Government taxation, the spirit became very popular across the country.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For much of the 1700s the area was a hotbed of gin smuggling - in 1795 alone a million gallons of gin are said to have been smuggled across the Solway.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And now gin distilling is set to return once again to Cumbria.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p><span></span></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"210\" src=\"/media/files/merchandise.jpg\" style=\"float: right;\" width=\"893\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(3791,'<p></p>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 237px; width: 777px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"449\" src=\"/media/files/brand/the_lakes_gin_2.jpg\" width=\"367\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>THE LAKES GIN</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Lakes Gin will be the only gin distilled in the Lake District, and will be available from Summer 2014.</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The LakesGinwill be a truly Cumbriangin, made with local botanicals, and distilled in our small artisan still.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The onlyginto be distilled in Cumbria, The LakesGinis a truly unique product. It will be carefully crafted using classicginbotanicals augmented with those native to Cumbria - including juniper, bilberry, heather and meadowsweet.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Made very much on an artisan, small batch scale, it will be lovingly created in our small 1,000 litre still, perfectly designed to produce an outstanding spirit. Instead of the rapid distillation found in most other mass producedgins, ours will be produced over 24 hours - very slowly, very carefully, very delicious.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\">Gin in Cumbria</span></h1>\n<hr><br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cumbria has a rich history of gin - not surprising when it is the main area in the UK where juniper grows.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Throughout the 18th century gin production in the Lake District flourished as, despite Government taxation, the spirit became very popular across the country.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For much of the 1700s the area was a hotbed of gin smuggling - in 1795 alone a million gallons of gin are said to have been smuggled across the Solway.</p>\n<br>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And now gin distilling is set to return once again to Cumbria.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p><span></span></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"210\" src=\"/media/files/merchandise.jpg\" style=\"float: right;\" width=\"893\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(3826,'<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"170\" src=\"/media/files/bbc_radio_4.jpg\" style=\"float: left; margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 15px;\" width=\"250\">BBC Radio 4 PM - 22.02.14</span></strong></p>\n<p></p>'),(3827,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(3875,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 459px; width: 951px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"451\" src=\"/media/files/brand/the_lakes_malt.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"362\"></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<h1>THE LAKES MALT</h1>\n<h3><span><span>The Lakes Malt will be available from 2019.</span></span></h3>\n<p>Most of the malt whisky we will produce will be lightly peated, so more akin to the whiskies from the highlands rather than Islay, although we do plan to run some batches of a more heavily peated malt each year.</p>\n<p><span>Our team is steeped in whisky experience. Our founder,</span><a href=\"http://213.175.215.219/~lakes2/our%20people/our-people/our-people/our-distillery/our-people/paul-currie\">Paul Currie</a><span>, co-founded the widely acclaimed, award winning Arran distillery, and our production is overseen by one of Scotlands foremost whisky experts,</span><a href=\"http://213.175.215.219/~lakes2/our-people/our-people/our-distillery/our-people/alan-rutherford\">Alan Rutherford</a><span>, former production director at Diageo and council member of the Scotch Whisky Association.</span></p>\n<p>Our master distiller<a href=\"http://213.175.215.219/~lakes2/our-distillery/our-people/chris-anderson\">Chris Anderson</a>will be crossing the border from Scotland, with a lifetimes experience of making the highest quality whisky, including as manager of a number of well known distilleries.</p>\n<p>The Lakes Malt will become available only once it is perfectly matured - so we will have to be patient for a little while yet!</p>\n<p>You can secure your own bottlings taken from the first 100 casks ever produced of The Lakes Malt by joining our Founders\' Club -<a href=\"/admin/cms/page/54/edit-plugin/142/founders-club\" target=\"_self\">Click Here</a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(3933,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4007,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4019,'<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"170\" src=\"/media/files/bbc_radio_4.jpg\" style=\"float: left; margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 15px;\" width=\"250\">BBC Radio 4 PM - 22.02.14</span></strong></p>\n<p></p>'),(4020,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4039,'<h3><span>From the outset it has been our aim at The Lakes Distillery to create not just world-class spirits but a destination for whisky lovers and a key attraction for visitors to the Lakes.</span></h3>'),(4040,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With the aim of introducing as many people as possible to The Lakes Distillery, we are offering a range of exclusive benefits to those who choose to become Members.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Membership is absolutely free and along with regular newsletters, members will enjoy advance notification of new products at The Lakes Distillery along with a whole range of privileges including 10% off all items in our online shop (excluding Founders and Connoisseurs memberships).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So, if you are a whisky lover, love the lakes or simply want to joi us on this great adventure,<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.lakesdistillery.com/register\">sign up now.</a></strong></span></p>'),(4043,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4049,'<h3><span>From the outset it has been our aim at The Lakes Distillery to create not just world-class spirits but a destination for whisky lovers and a key attraction for visitors to the Lakes.</span></h3>'),(4050,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With the aim of introducing as many people as possible to The Lakes Distillery, we are offering a range of exclusive benefits to those who choose to become Members.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Membership is absolutely free and along with regular newsletters, members will enjoy advance notification of new products at The Lakes Distillery along with a whole range of privileges including 10% off all items in our online shop (excluding Founders and Connoisseurs memberships).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So, if you are a whisky lover, love the lakes or simply want to joi us on this great adventure,<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.lakesdistillery.com/register\">sign up now.</a></strong></span></p>'),(4053,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4265,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4266,'<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span>Connoisseurs\' Club - 12,000</span></h2>\n<h3><span>Worldwide membership restricted to a maximum of 60</span></h3>'),(4267,'<p style=\"text-align: left;\">By becoming part of a very select group of just 60 Connoisseurs Club members, you will be writing your name in history. Your membership will include many unique benefits but by far the <em style=\"text-align: justify;\">most</em> exclusive is your very own Connoisseurs Cask.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"253\" src=\"/media/files/cask_and_bottles.jpg\" style=\"float: left; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 25px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px;\" width=\"450\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Lakes Distillery will produce 60 very special Connoisseurs Club oak sherry casks, into which the first distilling of The Lakes Malt will flow. Each cask is estimated to contain more than 100 bottles and you can be there on that historic first day to make the whisky yourself, fill your own Connoisseurs Cask and see it stored in the distillery warehouse. And that Connoisseurs Cask will forever bear your name.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can decide when you would like to bottle your exclusive whisky, and the duty, VAT and delivery is included in the cost of membership. You can either bottle it all at the same time, or spread the bottlings over 10 years. But this is more than just becoming part of the history of this magical spirit; it is truly an investment in its own right.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With over 100 bottles in each cask, and given the very unique nature of the malt whisky, taken from The Lakes Distillerys first ever production, it is estimated that the value of your cask could be in excess of *20,000.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An investment for head and the heart is a very rare thing indeed  The Connoisseurs Club is all this and more.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">In addition to your unique signature Connoisseurs Cask, you will exclusively enjoy:</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>\n<p>A yearly Connoisseurs Dinner, for you and a guest, when you can personally taste the maturing malt from your very own cask. This will also include overnight accommodation at the nearby 4-star Trout Hotel</p>\n<p></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>\n<p>A gift of a beautiful, commemorative limited edition print, taken from a specially commissioned painting of The Lakes Distillery</p>\n<p></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>\n<p>Invitations to exclusive events at the distillery</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>*Based on each bottle being worth around 200 after 10 years.</em></p>'),(4274,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4275,'<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span>Connoisseurs\' Club - 12,000</span></h2>\n<h3><span>Worldwide membership restricted to a maximum of 60</span></h3>'),(4276,'<p style=\"text-align: left;\">By becoming part of a very select group of just 60 Connoisseurs Club members, you will be writing your name in history. Your membership will include many unique benefits but by far the <em style=\"text-align: justify;\">most</em> exclusive is your very own Connoisseurs Cask.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"253\" src=\"/media/files/cask_and_bottles.jpg\" style=\"float: left; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 25px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px;\" width=\"450\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Lakes Distillery will produce 60 very special Connoisseurs Club oak sherry casks, into which the first distilling of The Lakes Malt will flow. Each cask is estimated to contain more than 100 bottles and you can be there on that historic first day to make the whisky yourself, fill your own Connoisseurs Cask and see it stored in the distillery warehouse. And that Connoisseurs Cask will forever bear your name.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can decide when you would like to bottle your exclusive whisky, and the duty, VAT and delivery is included in the cost of membership. You can either bottle it all at the same time, or spread the bottlings over 10 years. But this is more than just becoming part of the history of this magical spirit; it is truly an investment in its own right.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With over 100 bottles in each cask, and given the very unique nature of the malt whisky, taken from The Lakes Distillerys first ever production, it is estimated that the value of your cask could be in excess of *20,000.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">An investment for head and the heart is a very rare thing indeed  The Connoisseurs Club is all this and more.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">In addition to your unique signature Connoisseurs Cask, you will exclusively enjoy:</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>\n<p>A yearly Connoisseurs Dinner, for you and a guest, when you can personally taste the maturing malt from your very own cask. This will also include overnight accommodation at the nearby 4-star Trout Hotel</p>\n<p></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>\n<p>A gift of a beautiful, commemorative limited edition print, taken from a specially commissioned painting of The Lakes Distillery</p>\n<p></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>\n<p>Invitations to exclusive events at the distillery</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>*Based on each bottle being worth around 200 after 10 years.</em></p>'),(4306,'<p>Musk are expert providers of brewhouses and distillery equipment, Mash Tuns and Washback systems.</p>'),(4310,'<p>Musk are expert providers of brewhouses and distillery equipment, Mash Tuns and Washback systems.</p>'),(4313,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 884px; width: 884px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"449\" src=\"/media/files/brand/the_one_bottle.jpg\" width=\"367\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>THE ONE</h1>\n<h3>The One is a unique blend of exceptional whiskies from the British Isles.</h3>\n<p>Each has its own distinctive characteristics, resulting in a whisky of intriguing complexity.</p>\n<p>There are now distilleries producing whisky across the British Isles, and this has led us to create an entirely new concept in blended whiskies - a British Isles Blend.</p>\n<p>To create \'The One\', we have searched far and wide to bring together a range of very special whiskies from the British Isles. These have been blended with great care and passion to create a perfectly balanced whisky.</p>\n<h3>Tasting Notes</h3>\n<p>Slightly smoky, sweet and fruity, nutty, with hints of spice.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><a class=\"black_button\" href=\"/shop\" target=\"_self\" title=\"But it Now\">Buy It Now</a></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">Reviews</h1>\n<hr>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #ff9900; font-size: medium;\"><strong>The One - British Blend</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I Have just had the pleasure of Tasting this really pleasant this whisky. fresh &amp; smooth, kind on the palette,slightly peaty which lingers with citrus. Excellent First Production; The future should be promising.</p>\n<hr>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #ff9900; font-size: medium;\"><strong>The One - British blend</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sweet aroma, light, fresh Palette, Pear Drops, smooth feel Finish, liquorice, lingering Very nice blend - recommend <strong>3rd December 2013</strong></p>\n<hr>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #ff9900; font-size: medium;\"><strong>The One, hits the spot!</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I ordered a bottle of The One having heard it was well worth a try. Very pleased I did. Speedy and careful delivery. Thought I\'d keep it for Christmas, but it looked so good I tried it early. Very smooth, subtle peaty, smokey flavour. Goes great with water to let the complexity out without too much power. A delight to drink, well crafted blend bodes well for the Cumbrian whiskies to come. These boys know what they are doing. Strongly recommended. <strong>19th December 2013</strong></p>\n<hr>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A really quality blend this, crafted with obvious love<em>-<strong>Score 87</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Very nice. Well rounded sweet and spicy. A very enjoyable little blend, and not very expensive too. Lovely -<strong><em>Score 84</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The One is a good solid blend and well worth considering as we move into the winter months</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The design is simple and gorgeous</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Lovelycreamy sweet vanillafudgenote</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Its nicely sweet and well balanced</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Very nice blend - recommend</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Both The One whisky and Cumbria are equally beautiful</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"/media/files/brand/banner/bottom_banner_(1).jpg\" width=\"1000\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4317,'<p>Behind the scenes at the photoshoot for our ad campaign. Special thanks to Adam and the team at<a href=\"http://www.julesb.co.uk/\">Jules B</a> who dressed and styled the models.</p>'),(4381,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 493px; width: 903px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"449\" src=\"/media/files/brand/the_one_bottle.jpg\" width=\"367\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1></h1>\n<h1>THE ONE</h1>\n<p>The One is a unique blend of exceptional whiskie