s, and consequently the Lake District is home to numerous artisan food producers and craftsmen  all working with their surroundings to create something special. From Cumbrian cheeses to lamb and fish, the region is a cornucopia of great ingredients and our bar will stock wines, local ales and whiskies hand-picked to complement them.It has been our aim, from the early stages of planning The Lakes Distillery that, not only will our visitors be able to learn all about The Lakes Malt, The Lakes Gin &amp; The Lakes Vodka they will be able to see and taste for themselves other local produce in our artisan bar &amp; bistro.</p>'),(4423,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4424,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4471,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"width: 250px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr align=\"center\" valign=\"top\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<p><a href=\"/our-distillery/our-people/paul-currie-our-people\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"400\" src=\"/media/files/paul_currie_v2.jpg\" width=\"247\"></a></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<p><a href=\"/our-distillery/our-people/john-drake-our-people\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"400\" src=\"/media/files/john_drake_v2.jpg\" width=\"247\"></a></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"400\" src=\"/media/files/katie_read_v2.jpg\" width=\"247\"></p>\n</td>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"400\" src=\"/media/files/alan_rutherford_v2.jpg\" width=\"247\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"400\" src=\"/media/files/nigel_mills_v2.jpg\" width=\"247\"></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4614,''),(4619,''),(4639,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4640,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4642,'<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">VIEW OUR E-BROCHURE</h3>'),(4644,'<h3><span>Imagine if you could own one of the first bottles produced of one of the great single malts - well now you can. Strictly limited to the first 2975 applicants.</span></h3>'),(4650,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">By becoming a member of our Founders Club, you can join us on our journey, by receiving the very first bottles of the maturing Lakes Malt taken from the first 100 casks to be produced at the distillery.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is How it Works...</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will set aside the first 100 casks produced at the Lakes Distillery and we will bottle the maturing whisky for Founders Club members.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Each year for ten years you will receive one 70cl bottle giving you a collectible set of the distillerys first ever production, all with unique, limited edition labels. You will also receive two miniatures each year so you will have the rare opportunity to taste the spirit as it develops over time into a wonderful, single malt whisky. Delivery of the first bottle will be in 2015.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">These casks will not be available to the general public  only to members.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you join, you will also receive a membership pack with your certificate.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On-going benefits will include a bi-monthly newsletter with rare, limited edition offers, web cam access so you can follow all our progress at The Lakes Distillery and discount vouchers on food, beverages and distillery tours.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This offer will never be repeated. It is a rare opportunity to own a piece of historic whisky distilling.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">These first casks can only ever be produced once  so this is YOUR chance to own a piece of whisky history. Its going to be fascinating seeing how our spirit matures and we want connoisseurs and friends of the Lakes to be part of the journey.</p>'),(4652,'<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Life Membership</h3>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>\n<p>595 for those in the UK,Including VAT, duty and delivery to United Kingdom mainland addresses</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Monthly payments available for those in the UK. 100 a month over 6 months,Including VAT, duty and delivery to United Kingdom mainland addresses</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">695 in the EUIncluding VAT, duty and delivery to the EU. For other countries please contact us for further information</p>\n</li>\n</ul>'),(4722,'<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The distillery is located next to Bassenthwaite Lake, which is a National Nature Reserve in one of Britain\'s most beautiful areas, the Lake District.</span></h3>'),(4724,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Close to Bassenthwaite Lake, in an area of unimaginable beauty encircled by Cumbrian fells, we have found the perfect home for the new Lakes Distillery.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are renovating the historic buildings of an old Victorian Model Farm next to the famous river Derwent and close to Bassenthwaite Lake, and there we aim to produce a world class single malt whisky.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have ideal water from the famous River Derwent, with its source high up in the fells, a team steeped in whisky experience, and perfect conditions for distilling.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Derwent\'s source is at Sprinkling Tarn, one of the most beautiful tarns in Cumbria, and from there it flows down through the peaty foothills, which surround Scafell Pike, the highest of the Lakes\' peaks. It is a famous salmon river, and the area where it flows past our distillery has been designated a site of Special Scientific Interest. Analysis has shown it contains all the vital constituents necessary for distilling the purest whisky  but that is just the start of the process.</p>'),(4726,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have put a lot of thought into the production process at our distillery to ensure we produce a malt whisky of outstanding quality. The plant has been carefully designed to the highest specification, and our copper stills will be made to a unique design and on a small artisan scale  no mass production for us!</span><span style=\"font-size: medium; text-align: justify;\"><br></span></p>'),(4728,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The quality of the casks used for maturing has a major impact on the whisky and we will use a high proportion of sherry casks in addition to bourbon barrels  we may experiment with other different woods for our casks as well, as not being a scotch whisky we can use woods other than oak.<br>The moisture rich atmosphere of the Lakes will be ideal for the maturing process.<br>Most of the malt whisky we will produce will be lightly peated, so more akin to the whiskies from the highlands rather than Islay. However, we do plan to run some batches each year of a heavily peated malt.</p>'),(4730,'<p></p>\n<hr>\n<h1><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\"><strong>A \'GREEN\' WHISKY</strong></span></h1>\n<hr>\n<p><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Producing our whisky in the most environmentally friendly way possible is very important to us, and we will be doing everything possible to reduce our carbon footprint.</span></em></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><hr><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The whisky production process is entirely natural, using only grain, yeast and water. No damaging effluent is produced.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Most of the by-products from the distillation processes will be returned to local farmers for use as animal feed and for soil improvement.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Water used for production will be stored and recycled.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Heat from the distillation process will be reused to heat all the buildings (including the visitor centre), and natural ventilation and river water will be used for cooling.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Building materials will be as eco friendly as possible (eg wool insulation in the walls).</span></span></li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>'),(4763,'<h3>We are renovating the historic buildings of an old Victorian Model Farm next to the famous river Derwent and close to the lake, and there we aim to produce a world class single malt whisky.</h3>'),(4764,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 212px; width: 291px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Model farms were designed to be beautiful as well as functional  and our buildings are certainly beautiful and ideally suited to our needs. Each one is being carefully and sympathetically adapted, preserving the character and history of the old,stone-built barns and sheds.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"221\" src=\"/media/files/our_buildings/dsc04148.jpg\" width=\"629\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<p>The main barn will house our mash house and still house, with our unique stills, carefully designed to produce our Lakes Malt and Lakes Gin. An old cattle shed will be converted into our warehouse, with further cattle sheds being transformed into our shop and bistro. We think that Jos Christopherson, who farmed here in 1847, would have approved. Perhaps he even had an illicit still at the farm?</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4774,'<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This quatrefoil design of a four leaf clover can be foun<img alt=\"\" height=\"152\" src=\"/media/files/hope,_faith,_luck,_love_v6_.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 15px; float: left;\" width=\"250\">d throughout the distillery buildings  representing hope, faith, love and luck. We hope to have all four in abundance!</span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"></span></p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4775,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4776,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4781,'<h3>Production will start in Spring 2014, with the visitor centre opening in the autumn.</h3>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 270px; width: 455px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"10\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"644\" src=\"/media/files/timetable/timetable_(2).gif\" width=\"161\"></td>\n<td>\n<p><span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong>September 2013</strong></em></span></span></p>\n<p><span>- Launch of<a href=\"/shop\">The ONE</a>at the Taste Cumbria festival</span></p>\n<p><span><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">October 2013</span></em></strong></span></p>\n<p><span>- Final stages of planning being approved</span></p>\n<p><span>- Interior designers working on their initial concepts</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em><strong>November 2013</strong></em></span></p>\n<p>- Work to start on site</p>\n<p>- Gift packs and miniature gift packs launched in time for Christmas!</p>\n<p>- The Wine Chambers Christmas tasting at the Grand Hotel - Tynemouth, Newcastle Upon Tyne. 27th &amp; 28th 5pm - 9pm</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><em>Spring 2014</em></strong></span></p>\n<p>- The stills will be delivered allowing us to start the production of The Lakes Gin, and The Lakes Malt straight away</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><em>Autumn 2014</em></strong></span></p>\n<p>- We hope to have the remaining building work completed for our Visitor Centre, Bistro &amp; Bar and Shop</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4784,'<h3><span>You will be able to go inside the distillery to see exactly how The Lakes Malt and The Lakes Gin are made, as well as being able to visit our warehouse filled with our maturing whisky.</span></h3>\n<p><img src=\"/media/files/destillery_tours/slate.gif\" width=\"660\" alt=\"\" height=\"126\"></p>\n<p>The Lake District is a hugely popular tourist area, and we aim to be a major attraction to the 15 million visitors who come each year.<img src=\"/media/files/destillery_tours/archway-in-dis.gif\" width=\"200\" style=\"float: right;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p>The tour will start in an information area which will include a video, and your expert, entertaining guide will then take you through to the distillery to reveal the secrets of how malt whisky and gin are made. You will be taken through the warehouse, where our whisky peacefully matures in casks, and on to our tasting room, where you can taste our products for yourself.</p>\n<p></p>'),(4793,'<h3>The water we will use to create The Lakes Malt is from the famous river Derwent, which emerges from Bassenthwaite Lake next to the distillery.</h3>'),(4794,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 206px; width: 592px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"300\" src=\"/media/files/production/archways.gif\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"169\"></td>\n<td>\n<p>The quality of the casks used for maturing has a major impact on the whisky and we will use a high proportion of sherry casks in addition to bourbon barrels  we may experiment with other different woods for our casks as well. The moisture rich atmosphere of the Lakes will be ideal for the maturing process. Most of the malt whisky we will produce will be lightly peated, so more akin to the whiskies from the highlands rather than Islay. However, we do plan to run some batches each year of a peated malt.</p>\n<p>Our team is steeped in whisky experience. Our founder, Paul Currie, co-founded the widely acclaimed, award winning Arran distillery, and our production is overseen by one of Scotlands foremost whisky experts, Alan Rutherford, former production director at Diageo and council member of the Scotch Whisky Association.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4795,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 193px; width: 622px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our master distiller, Chris Anderson will be crossing the border from Scotland, with a lifetimes experience of making the highest quality whisky, including as manager of a number of well known distilleries.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With all this expertise we aim to produce a single malt to rival the finest our Scottish neighbours can produce - and we are giving those who love whisky, who love the Lake District or who simply want to embark on a wonderful adventure the chance to own the very first bottles with our<a href=\"/members/founders-club\">Founders\' Club</a>.</p>\n</td>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"300\" src=\"/media/files/production/pc_+_chris_anderson_(2)_(1).jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"230\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4796,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 221px; width: 576px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>We have put a lot of thought into the production process at our distillery to ensure we produce a malt whisky of outstanding quality. The plant has been carefully designed to the highest specification, with a new innovation we will use both copper and stainless steel condensers to create a whisky of richer character. Our copper stills will be made to a unique design and on a small artisan scale  no mass production for us!</p>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"187\" src=\"/media/files/production/warehouse.gif\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"253\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4797,'<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"142\" src=\"/media/files/production/sprinkling-tarn.gif\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"254\"></td>\n<td>\n<p>Its source is at Sprinkling Tarn, one of the most beautiful tarns in Cumbria, and from there it flows down through the peaty foothills, which surround Scafell Pike, the highest of the Lakes\' peaks. Analysis has shown it contains all the vital constituents necessary for distilling the purest whisky  but that is just the start of the process.</p>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4835,'<h3>The water we will use to create The Lakes Malt is from the famous river Derwent, which emerges from Bassenthwaite Lake next to the distillery.</h3>'),(4836,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 206px; width: 592px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"300\" src=\"/media/files/production/archways.gif\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"169\"></td>\n<td>\n<p>The quality of the casks used for maturing has a major impact on the whisky and we will use a high proportion of sherry casks in addition to bourbon barrels  we may experiment with other different woods for our casks as well. The moisture rich atmosphere of the Lakes will be ideal for the maturing process. Most of the malt whisky we will produce will be lightly peated, so more akin to the whiskies from the highlands rather than Islay. However, we do plan to run some batches each year of a peated malt.</p>\n<p>Our team is steeped in whisky experience. Our founder, Paul Currie, co-founded the widely acclaimed, award winning Arran distillery, and our production is overseen by one of Scotlands foremost whisky experts, Alan Rutherford, former production director at Diageo and council member of the Scotch Whisky Association.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4837,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 193px; width: 622px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our master distiller, Chris Anderson will be crossing the border from Scotland, with a lifetimes experience of making the highest quality whisky, including as manager of a number of well known distilleries.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With all this expertise we aim to produce a single malt to rival the finest our Scottish neighbours can produce - and we are giving those who love whisky, who love the Lake District or who simply want to embark on a wonderful adventure the chance to own the very first bottles with our<a href=\"/members/founders-club\">Founders\' Club</a>.</p>\n</td>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"300\" src=\"/media/files/production/pc_+_chris_anderson_(2)_(1).jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"230\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4838,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 221px; width: 576px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>We have put a lot of thought into the production process at our distillery to ensure we produce a malt whisky of outstanding quality. The plant has been carefully designed to the highest specification, with a new innovation we will use both copper and stainless steel condensers to create a whisky of richer character. Our copper stills will be made to a unique design and on a small artisan scale  no mass production for us!</p>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"187\" src=\"/media/files/production/warehouse.gif\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"253\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4839,'<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img alt=\"\" height=\"142\" src=\"/media/files/production/sprinkling-tarn.gif\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" width=\"254\"></td>\n<td>\n<p>Its source is at Sprinkling Tarn, one of the most beautiful tarns in Cumbria, and from there it flows down through the peaty foothills, which surround Scafell Pike, the highest of the Lakes\' peaks. Analysis has shown it contains all the vital constituents necessary for distilling the purest whisky  but that is just the start of the process.</p>\n<p></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4844,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4845,'<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4848,'<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"620\" src=\"/media/files/the_bar_and_bistro/545_big.jpg\" style=\"vertical-align: text-top;\" width=\"620\"></p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4853,'<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Work is now underway to convert one of our cattle sheds into a bar and bistro which we hope will be the perfect place in which to sample some truly impressive Whisky, Gin and Vodka alongside a menu full of locally-sourced and seasonal dishes.</p>'),(4855,'<h3><span>From Cumbrian cheeses to lamb and fish, the region is a cornucopia of great ingredients and our bar will stock wines, local ales and whiskies hand-picked to complement them.</span></h3>'),(4856,'<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Many before us have realised that this unspoiled corner of Britain is a treasure trove of ingredients and resources, and consequently the Lake District is home to numerous artisan food producers and craftsmen  all working with their surroundings to create something special. From Cumbrian cheeses to lamb and fish, the region is a cornucopia of great ingredients and our bar will stock wines, local ales and whiskies hand-picked to complement them.It has been our aim, from the early stages of planning The Lakes Distillery that, not only will our visitors be able to learn all about The Lakes Malt, The Lakes Gin &amp; The Lakes Vodka they will be able to see and taste for themselves other local produce in our artisan bar &amp; bistro.</p>'),(4859,'<h3><span>You will be able to see here our artisan bar and bistros delicious menu.</span></h3>'),(4860,'<table style=\"height: 194px; width: 579px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/scone.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/while_you_decide.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/north_atlantic_prawn.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0110.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0122.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0152.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4863,'<h3><span>We will be converting one of the byres at the site into a very special private dining facility, with access into our warehouse for exclusive tastings.</span></h3>'),(4868,'<h3><span>You will be able to see here our artisan bar and bistros delicious menu.</span></h3>'),(4869,'<table style=\"height: 194px; width: 579px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/scone.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/while_you_decide.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/north_atlantic_prawn.jpg\" width=\"213\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0110.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0122.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/menus/_mg_0152.jpg\" width=\"214\" alt=\"\" height=\"320\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4876,'<h3><span>The ONE is not only perfect alone but great in cocktails. We have had some fantastic cocktail tutorial videos created so you too can make you own cocktails with The ONE.</span></h3>'),(4877,'<table border=\"0\" style=\"height: 296px; width: 597px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE SOUR ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE OLD ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"147\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/thesourone-easy.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/sour-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"147\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/thesourone-easy.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/old-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"147\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/theoldone-advanced.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\"><hr></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE IRISH ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE BLUE ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h2><span style=\"font-size: large;\">THE SMOKEY ONE</span></h2>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/irish-one/\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"148\" src=\"/media/files/coctails/theirishone-medium.jpg\" width=\"197\"></a></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"/bistro-and-bar/cocktails/blue-one/\"