h3>'),(4906,'<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE - British blend<img alt=\"\" height=\"20\" src=\"http://redhooklibrary.org/files/2013/11/five-stars.png\" width=\"100\"></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sweet aroma, light, fresh Palette, Pear Drops, smooth feel Finish, liquorice, lingering Very nice blend - recommend</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE, hits the spot!</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I ordered a bottle of The One having heard it was well worth a try. Very pleased I did. Speedy and careful delivery. Thought I\'d keep it for Christmas, but it looked so good I tried it early. Very smooth, subtle peaty, smokey flavour. Goes great with water to let the complexity out without too much power. A delight to drink, well crafted blend bodes well for the Cumbrian whiskies to come. These boys know what they are doing. Strongly recommended.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE - British Blend<img alt=\"\" height=\"20\" src=\"http://redhooklibrary.org/files/2013/11/five-stars.png\" style=\"font-size: 2em;\" width=\"100\"></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I Have just had the pleasure of Tasting this really pleasant this whisky. fresh &amp; smooth, kind on the palette,slightly peaty which lingers with citrus. Excellent First Production; The future should be promising.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE<img alt=\"\" height=\"20\" src=\"http://redhooklibrary.org/files/2013/11/five-stars.png\" style=\"font-size: 2em;\" width=\"100\"></h1>\n<p>Brilliant found you at Kendal food fair on Sunday I live in Cumbria where can I buy do tell us.</p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4939,'<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE - British blend<img alt=\"\" height=\"20\" src=\"http://redhooklibrary.org/files/2013/11/five-stars.png\" width=\"100\"></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sweet aroma, light, fresh Palette, Pear Drops, smooth feel Finish, liquorice, lingering Very nice blend - recommend</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE, hits the spot!</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I ordered a bottle of The One having heard it was well worth a try. Very pleased I did. Speedy and careful delivery. Thought I\'d keep it for Christmas, but it looked so good I tried it early. Very smooth, subtle peaty, smokey flavour. Goes great with water to let the complexity out without too much power. A delight to drink, well crafted blend bodes well for the Cumbrian whiskies to come. These boys know what they are doing. Strongly recommended.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE - British Blend<img alt=\"\" height=\"20\" src=\"http://redhooklibrary.org/files/2013/11/five-stars.png\" style=\"font-size: 2em;\" width=\"100\"></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I Have just had the pleasure of Tasting this really pleasant this whisky. fresh &amp; smooth, kind on the palette,slightly peaty which lingers with citrus. Excellent First Production; The future should be promising.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ONE<img alt=\"\" height=\"20\" src=\"http://redhooklibrary.org/files/2013/11/five-stars.png\" style=\"font-size: 2em;\" width=\"100\"></h1>\n<p>Brilliant found you at Kendal food fair on Sunday I live in Cumbria where can I buy do tell us.</p>\n<p></p>\n<hr>\n<p></p>'),(4940,'<p>Building work continues on site. The roof over the production area of the distillery is well underway, the builders are making fantastic progress! You can watch them while they work on our webcams <a href=\"/our-distillery/webcams/\">click here</a></p>'),(4943,'<p>Behind the scenes at the photoshoot for our ad campaign. Special thanks to Adam and the team at<a href=\"http://www.julesb.co.uk/\">Jules B</a> who dressed and styled the models.</p>'),(4945,'<p>Building work continues on site. The roof over the production area of the distillery is well underway, the builders are making fantastic progress! You can watch them while they work on our webcams <a href=\"/our-distillery/webcams/\">click here</a></p>'),(4953,'<table style=\"height: 308px; width: 838px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/paul_currie_at_site.jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>PAUL CURRIE - FOUNDER AND MANAGING DIRECTOR</h1>\n<hr>\n<p><span><span><span>Whiskys been a part of my life for as long as I can remember.</span></span></span></p>\n<hr>\n<p>With a family background in the whisky industry, he has had a lifelong love of spirits, and previously set up the award winning Isle of Arran distillery with his father. He has been the driving force behind setting up the new Lakes Distillery.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4954,'<table style=\"height: 308px; width: 905px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_alan_rutherford.jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>DR ALAN RUTHERFORD OBE - DIRECTOR</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>The Lakes Distillery has so much going for it  a great team, a wonderful location, and all the ingredients for what should be an outstanding malt whisky</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Alan Rutherford, whose career in the whisky industry spans almost 40 years, is one of the leading figures in the whisky industry. A former council member of the Scotch Whisky Council, he was previously scotch whisky production director at United Distillers - later Diageo. Alan will oversee the production of our whiskies and gin.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4955,'<table style=\"height: 310px; width: 901px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_chris_anderson_(2).jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>CHRIS ANDERSON - MASTER DISTILLER</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>\"Most of all Im looking forward to seeing the first spirit flow into the spirit safe. Then the adventure really begins.\"</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Chris Anderson comes from a long line of Scottish whisky distillers and began his own whisky career at CaolIla on Islay. He also worked at Lagavulin before moving to manage all of Dewars distilleries, including Royal Brackla, Aberfeldy, Craigellachie and Aultmore. Chris brings a wealth of experience to us, as he will play the central role in creating the new Lakes Malt.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4974,'<table style=\"height: 308px; width: 905px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_alan_rutherford.jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>DR ALAN RUTHERFORD OBE - DIRECTOR</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>The Lakes Distillery has so much going for it  a great team, a wonderful location, and all the ingredients for what should be an outstanding malt whisky</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Alan Rutherford, whose career in the whisky industry spans almost 40 years, is one of the leading figures in the whisky industry. A former council member of the Scotch Whisky Council, he was previously scotch whisky production director at United Distillers - later Diageo. Alan will oversee the production of our whiskies and gin.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>'),(4975,'<table style=\"height: 310px; width: 901px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/media/files/our_people/pc_+_chris_anderson_(2).jpg\" width=\"230\" style=\"margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\" height=\"300\" alt=\"\"></td>\n<td>\n<h1>CHRIS ANDERSON - MASTER DISTILLER</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>\"Most of all Im looking forward to seeing the first spirit flow into the spirit safe. Then the adventure really begins.\"</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Chris Ande